                <note rend="inline" type="source">662.6331/69</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State of a Conversation With
                        the Italian Ambassador</hi> (<hi rend="italic">De Martino</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-26">March 26,
                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>During the call today of the Italian Ambassador he brought up the question of the
                    customs union. I told him that I had had nothing <pb facs="0685" n="571"
                        xml:id="pg_571"/> to say on that subject and neither had the Department of
                    Commerce and that reports to the contrary were inaccurate. He said he understood
                    that. He further stated that Italy had been inclined to favor it but that was
                    merely tentative.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>H[<hi rend="smallcaps">enry</hi>] L. S[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >timson</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
